<br>
I started EQ when SoL came out (or thereabout)<br>
<br>
There now you know my background...<br>
<br>
First of all id like to say thx for the many comments on the monkey nerf in here. I had expected much more glee at the fate monkeys may be facing.<br>
<br>
(From the sound of the trolls at the monkeyboards the entire Warrior community is pointing fingers and lauging at us... but i guess only the bad seeds ceased the opportunity to pour salt in the wounds of the monkeys.)<br>
<br>
I agree with what everyone in here says basically.<br>
<br>
It was warriors/plateclasses who neded to be fixed.. not monkeys nerfed. The monks that are disrupting the ballance as i see it are the monkeys with 1450 AC and 4000 HP un/selfbuffed, because as a non twink monkey that started from naked lvl 1, I can assure you i dont stand up very long against mobs that require a raid sized force to deal with.<br>
<br>
As for monkeys holding aggro.. well, heh our agro depend on our dmg output. Warrior losing aggro to us while taunting is just wrong. the Taunt skill needs to be looked at. For sure!<br>
<br>
Im not all too familiar with the game mechanics when it comes to actual AC influence vs exp mobs and raidmobs, but i get the feeling that decreasing monkey dmg mitigation and increasing the avoidance will allow for even better survival vs uber mobs, since the common monkey AC is just too low to make a difference anyway. (im at 1040 AC or there around) But time will tell as the patch is released.<br>
<br>
The monks fears as to what will happen to our &quot;survivability&quot; when pulling... Well many say VI never intended for mobs to be &quot;pulled&quot; in the firstplace.. so i guess its just in line with &quot;the vision&quot; that we will have a hardertime pulling... Ways to work around it will arise im sure... (tag-chain comes to mind... Will require a few more monkeys in a guild tho, but...)<br>
<br>
And last point. monkeys soloability. Im 59.. as stated before... and im just now beginning to be able to solo a lower HP spider in Velks.. (example) so im stoked im even killing mobs that con dark blue to me.<br>
<br>
Twinked out iksar monkeys with fungi shoudnt be the standard against what monkeys are meassured... Im human and i have neiter fungi nor any other from of regen. That said i think the &quot;common&quot; monkey will agree that soloing is limited.. and hard.<br>
<br>
I know warriors dont have mush chance to solo either unless in very good gear.<br>
That im my opinion is wrong. Im somewhat of a casual to commited player. I average 4 hrs per night id say.. more on weekends less on weeknights. sometime i dont have more than 1 hr to spend online, and id like to be able to log myc favourite char, be it Warr, monkey, rogue or druid, and just kill a few mobs and still feel that ive spent the hour advancing my character. As it stands now, the classes with lesser solo abilities may not even bother logging in for just an hr... that in my opinion is sad. <br>
<br>
Since EQ is a multiplayer online game scocializing and grouping with others should indeed be promoted, but not enforced. exp in groups should be better than solo, to reward ppl who work together, but it shouldnt be the only way to do it...<br>
<br>
That said, i hope that any &quot;solo-envy&quot; that may be directed towards monkeys may be lightened up a lil. Instead i think actions should be taken towards giving all classes some degree of soloability.<br>
<br>
-edit- I dont have my epic yet either...<br>
<br>
<br>
-If you keep tanking ill keep die trying to pull.<br>
<br>
/Sai<br>
<br>
