<br>
Prenerf - Endgame monks can &amp; will con't pull &amp; tank level 75 mobs better then Plate class.<br>
Postnerf - Endgame monks will con't to tank level 75 mobs better then before, SK will pull better due to pure ac loss.<br>
<br>
Plain &amp; simple - Avoidance is much more powerful then AC verses those mobs because of the insane attack ratio.  Even with 2k ac, Warrior would still get hit for max dmg a majority of the time even with defensive.  A monk with VT gear would prob like the increase avoidance for tanking, because they are leaps &amp; bounds over the soft cap.  <br>
<br>
Easy solution make AC matter, VI doesn't need to give Warrior a 240 dodge skill, (which doesn't make since for a plate class in my mind) just a make real difference with between an ac of 1300 &amp; 1600.  It is just that simple.  <br>
<br>
Monks die enough trying pull ToV, HoT etc, esp in those 55-60 level range with average gear learning the ropes<br>
<br>
Decreasing ac, will hurt 99% of us where it really counts, pulling &amp; splitting mobs for our guild/group plain &amp; simple. <br>
<br>
As far as soloing goes, not ever monk has a fungi/t-staff/cof &amp; other godly high end loot to play with, fix ac &amp; let us get back to our jobs<br>
